1
00:01:51,370 --> 00:01:56,330
2.. 5..7.. 10 minutes..
he continued to stare.

2
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:59,450
I ignored him at first
but then I went to the table..

3
00:01:59,540 --> 00:02:01,700
..and I said, any problem, sir?

4
00:02:02,330 --> 00:02:03,580
I'm very sorry.

5
00:02:03,660 --> 00:02:06,500
You look like someone
I know, he replied

6
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:08,540
I was going to walk away..

7
00:02:08,620 --> 00:02:10,500
..but he was a 70 year old man.

8
00:02:10,750 --> 00:02:11,950
Horny uncle!

9
00:02:13,450 --> 00:02:16,660
Anyway, so I had to ask
him whom did I look like.

10
00:02:17,540 --> 00:02:18,870
Any guesses on his reply?

11
00:02:19,410 --> 00:02:20,330
His mother?

12
00:02:20,660 --> 00:02:22,200
His daughter.

13
00:02:23,450 --> 00:02:25,160
His 8th grade biology teacher.

14
00:02:25,450 --> 00:02:26,910
Don't try to fit in your fantasy here.

15
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,750
She was so hot, Mrs. Matthews..
I promise. Oh my god!

16
00:02:29,830 --> 00:02:34,000
He said I look like his dog.

17
00:02:37,540 --> 00:02:39,330
What? I'm serious!

18
00:02:39,870 --> 00:02:42,370
I'm serious.
His dog was called Princess.

19
00:02:42,450 --> 00:02:43,330
That's a terrible name.

20
00:02:43,410 --> 00:02:44,910
Forget the name, listen to the story.

21
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:48,000
I said, you made fun of me, uncle.
Can I go home now?

22
00:02:48,450 --> 00:02:51,370
He said, please listen to me.

23
00:02:52,370 --> 00:02:55,910
Princess died in
a car accident in 1985.

24
00:02:56,410 --> 00:02:59,950
She freed herself and
ran into an oncoming car.

25
00:03:00,410 --> 00:03:03,330
The car ran over her and by the
time he reached there, she was dead.

26
00:03:03,410 --> 00:03:05,540
She was dead. Her throat was crushed.

27
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,370
This happened on 17th June, 1985.

28
00:03:08,830 --> 00:03:09,950
You're joking. - No.

29
00:03:10,580 --> 00:03:11,870
That's my birthdate.

30
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,410
No.. - Yeah!

31
00:03:13,870 --> 00:03:17,120
And it gets stranger because
I have a birth mark on my neck.

32
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:18,330
Lying!

33
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,830
I have a birth mark on my neck.

34
00:03:21,750 --> 00:03:22,700
See!

35
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:30,080
Very funny.

36
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:33,120
Shaan.. I'm sorry.

37
00:03:33,620 --> 00:03:36,540
Shaan.. Shaan!

38
00:04:24,370 --> 00:04:26,200
Gulp it down, you'll feel better.

39
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,120
What happened?

40
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:36,160
Half of the critics hadn't
Even arrived, you should've waited.

41
00:04:36,250 --> 00:04:39,040
I don't know why but
I suddenly felt so weird.

42
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:42,830
I saw something that wasn't
actually there, but it felt so real.

43
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:44,750
I don't understand
what you are saying, Mehak

44
00:04:45,370 --> 00:04:46,370
I don't know.

45
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:49,120
You're okay now, right? - Yes.

46
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:51,700
Because everyone
really liked your work.

47
00:04:51,830 --> 00:04:53,330
You think? - Yes.

48
00:04:56,540 --> 00:04:58,580
Stop, pull over.

49
00:05:02,750 --> 00:05:03,580
Come up.

50
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:05,120
Why?

51
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:08,910
We'll have a drink,
listen to some music.

52
00:05:09,450 --> 00:05:10,330
You know..

53
00:05:11,290 --> 00:05:12,580
Just because it happened
once after getting drunk..

54
00:05:12,620 --> 00:05:14,120
..doesn't mean it's
gonna happen every time.

55
00:05:22,540 --> 00:05:25,040
You know what,
I don't know about your past life..

56
00:05:25,330 --> 00:05:29,330
But in this life you definitely are..
a princess

57
00:05:31,450 --> 00:05:32,370
Bye-bye.

58
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:35,540
Bye! - Goodnight.

59
00:05:35,580 --> 00:05:36,450
Goodnight.

60
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,370
Hello.. madam?

61
00:08:26,330 --> 00:08:27,250
Oh my God!

62
00:08:28,580 --> 00:08:30,580
Ma'am, are you ok?
- Ma'am, are you ok?

63
00:08:30,660 --> 00:08:32,500
Get some water! - What happened?

64
00:08:32,580 --> 00:08:34,370
She's bleeding! - Get some water.

65
00:08:34,450 --> 00:08:36,120
What happened?
- Have you found any ID?

66
00:08:48,580 --> 00:08:51,080
Mehak, open your mouth.
Show your tongue.

67
00:08:51,450 --> 00:08:54,620
Hold my hand. You're in a hospital,
I'm a doctor. Just relax.

68
00:08:54,910 --> 00:08:57,750
Show your tongue. Calm down.
You're in hospital. Open your eyes.

69
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:01,330
Open your eyes.

70
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:37,120
C'mon, Mehak.
The doctor has been waiting for long.

71
00:09:46,040 --> 00:09:49,080
I was six and you were
around three years old.

72
00:09:49,250 --> 00:09:51,580
Do you remember the
terrace on our Jammu home?

73
00:09:52,410 --> 00:09:54,620
I was spinning you around in circles..

74
00:09:54,700 --> 00:09:56,910
..when you suddenly
slipped out of my hand.

75
00:09:57,580 --> 00:09:59,040
You fell to the ground floor.

76
00:09:59,830 --> 00:10:02,200
Do you remember that song that
dad sang to calm you down..

77
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:32,200
Relax, Mehak.
You can't step out right..

78
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:35,660
..that's why I've brought
the outside world to you here.

79
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:38,910
Oh my god!

80
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:42,120
This is virtual therapy.

81
00:10:42,830 --> 00:10:46,870
For people like you.
Go on, walk ahead.

82
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:54,500
Very good, Mehak.

83
00:10:55,410 --> 00:10:56,870
Do you like shopping?

84
00:10:57,700 --> 00:11:00,410
Anusha told me that you
always did the grocery shopping.

85
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:03,580
C'mon, Mehak, keep going.

86
00:11:06,580 --> 00:11:09,750
That's good, Mehak.
So what do you feel like buying today?

87
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:11,540
Buy me a chocolate, aunty.

88
00:11:11,660 --> 00:11:13,580
Yes, pick up a chocolate for Joey.

89
00:11:14,830 --> 00:11:16,950
You can do it, Mehak.
- The biscuit ones.

90
00:11:17,660 --> 00:11:19,410
Biscuit chocolate, c'mon Mehak.

91
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:22,120
Where's the chocolate?

92
00:11:22,450 --> 00:11:23,830
There are people there.

93
00:11:23,910 --> 00:11:25,870
Please.. please.. - No, no.

94
00:11:25,950 --> 00:11:29,040
Please don't touch it. Mehak.
Please don't touch it.

95
00:11:29,290 --> 00:11:30,450
Keep going.

96
00:11:31,290 --> 00:11:33,700
You're almost there, Mehak. Relax.

97
00:11:35,750 --> 00:11:37,160
Look for the chocolate.

98
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:41,000
You can do it, Mehak.

99
00:11:42,370 --> 00:11:44,950
Be brave. Very good.

100
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,330
She hit me. - Who hit you?

101
00:11:51,410 --> 00:11:53,580
Relax.. relax..
- She hit me! She hit me!

102
00:11:53,620 --> 00:11:55,750
Relax. Mehak! Mehak!

103
00:11:55,870 --> 00:11:58,160
Mummy! - She hit me!

104
00:11:58,250 --> 00:11:59,450
Calm down. - Mummy!

105
00:11:59,540 --> 00:12:01,750
Relax, relax. - Don't touch me!

106
00:12:02,450 --> 00:12:04,160
Mehak!

107
00:12:07,660 --> 00:12:09,580
What happened to aunty? - Nothing.

108
00:12:11,410 --> 00:12:13,620
Go, get your drawing book.

109
00:12:19,580 --> 00:12:22,660
I'm sorry, Anusha.
Mehak suffers from Agoraphobia.

110
00:12:23,620 --> 00:12:27,290
She has a deep-seated
fear of the outside world.

111
00:12:27,750 --> 00:12:30,370
She's not being difficult,
she's just unwell.

112
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:34,580
If not treated,
Mehak can become completely unstable.

113
00:12:36,370 --> 00:12:38,500
She is certain that if
she steps out of the house..

114
00:12:38,580 --> 00:12:40,410
She will be made to experience the
same horror she went through that night.

115
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:42,910
But that taxi driver is in prison.

116
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,830
Mehak knows that very well.

117
00:12:44,910 --> 00:12:46,160
He can't do anything now.

118
00:12:46,250 --> 00:12:48,870
What happened that night?
It's not like she was raped!

119
00:12:55,700 --> 00:13:00,620
I understand, Anusha. If you want,
you can admit her to the clinic.

120
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:03,580
There is a good clinic in Byculla..
- Just a second, doctor.

121
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:07,620
There's no need to put Mehak in an
institution. And please, she's not crazy.

122
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:16,200
Take it.

123
00:13:18,580 --> 00:13:19,700
Thanks.

124
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:33,330
I don't want to talk,
I just need some time.

125
00:13:33,950 --> 00:13:36,040
Do you know how long its been
since you stepped out of this house?

126
00:13:36,870 --> 00:13:38,160
Two weeks. - Two?

127
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:41,080
Four. - Yes, four weeks.

128
00:13:41,160 --> 00:13:42,950
Not four weeks, but four months.

129
00:13:44,910 --> 00:13:45,700
That's true.

130
00:13:49,250 --> 00:13:50,700
What crap!

131
00:13:51,580 --> 00:13:54,200
Mehak, I have other
responsibilities as well.

132
00:13:54,290 --> 00:13:55,450
Did you see Joey today?

133
00:13:55,540 --> 00:13:57,580
He gets so frightened seeing
you that he can't sleep at night.

134
00:13:57,620 --> 00:14:00,080
Then why do you call
that therapist home?

135
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:02,910
What have I done?
It's always my fault!

136
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:06,500
He is a five year old kid, don't
you feel he deserves some normalcy?

137
00:14:08,330 --> 00:14:09,700
Are you blaming me for that?

138
00:14:10,700 --> 00:14:13,410
If he wants normalcy,
take him to his father. - Mehak.

139
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:16,330
Her kid gets screwed up,
is it my responsibility?

140
00:14:16,410 --> 00:14:18,120
Mehak, it's not
necessary to involve him.

141
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:20,370
And I'm just talking about Joey,
let's just stay there.

142
00:14:20,450 --> 00:14:22,950
What happened last week?
Tell him. - Get lost seriously.

143
00:14:23,410 --> 00:14:25,080
Joey returns from school
and rings the doorbell.

144
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:27,580
But he isn't able to
get into the house. Why?

145
00:14:27,660 --> 00:14:29,370
I wanna know that.
- How many times will she say that!

146
00:14:29,450 --> 00:14:30,540
Exactly!
- She's said it thrice already!

147
00:14:30,580 --> 00:14:33,250
I'll say it again and again, the kid
stood on the street for four hours.

148
00:14:33,330 --> 00:14:34,750
Why couldn't he get into the house?

149
00:14:34,950 --> 00:14:38,450
Because you couldn't go upto
the door and let him in.

150
00:14:38,540 --> 00:14:39,500
Yes. - Yes, so?

151
00:14:39,580 --> 00:14:42,700
I said I'm sorry. - What if
something had happened to the kid?

152
00:14:45,450 --> 00:14:47,450
I'm sorry. - What do I do?

153
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:50,580
What do I do? Quit my job?

154
00:14:51,580 --> 00:14:55,080
Shall I shop for normalcy from that
virtual supermarket for you?

155
00:14:55,290 --> 00:14:56,200
What do you want?

156
00:14:56,910 --> 00:14:58,620
What do you want? - What do you want?

157
00:14:58,700 --> 00:15:00,200
You want to send me to an institution!

158
00:15:00,290 --> 00:15:01,330
I don't want to send you
to an institution.. - Shut up!

159
00:15:01,410 --> 00:15:03,080
I heard you.

160
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:04,450
What did you hear? - Mehak.

161
00:15:05,330 --> 00:15:06,500
I'm feeling dizzy.

162
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:10,120
Ok.. calm down.. sit down.

163
00:15:10,580 --> 00:15:11,580
Sit down.

164
00:15:12,540 --> 00:15:13,660
Look, Mehak.

165
00:15:13,910 --> 00:15:16,450
You can't throw me
out of my own house.

166
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,870
This house belongs to me too.
- Of course, Mehak.

167
00:15:19,080 --> 00:15:20,500
It'll always be your house.

168
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:22,830
I'm just telling you that..

169
00:15:23,910 --> 00:15:24,950
Mehak?

170
00:15:29,750 --> 00:15:33,040
Anusha, be strong. We need to do this.

171
00:15:34,160 --> 00:15:35,580
I don't know if we're
doing the right thing.

172
00:15:35,620 --> 00:15:38,040
Anu, I'm taking responsibility.

173
00:15:40,870 --> 00:15:43,540
Trust me, she'll become fine in
a new place. Away from you guys.

174
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:55,370
Jiya?

175
00:16:03,870 --> 00:16:05,120
Jiya?

176
00:16:07,290 --> 00:16:08,750
Jiya!

177
00:16:12,540 --> 00:16:13,580
Oh!

178
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:16,370
Hi, ma'am - Go!

179
00:16:16,700 --> 00:16:18,750
Who are you? - I didn't do anything.

180
00:16:19,160 --> 00:16:22,450
Mehak.. please.. calm down.

181
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:24,200
Relax.

182
00:16:25,620 --> 00:16:27,290
It's me. - Where were you?

183
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:33,120
I can't.. I can't move.

184
00:16:33,450 --> 00:16:34,500
You got scared.

185
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:36,700
Who are you? How did you get in?

186
00:16:36,910 --> 00:16:38,080
The door was open.

187
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:41,830
I'm Manu. Manu Malhotra,
your next-door neighbour.

188
00:16:41,910 --> 00:16:42,910
I stay in
602.

189
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:45,250
I'm so sorry if I frightened you.

190
00:16:45,330 --> 00:16:47,580
I thought that Jiya was back. - Jiya?

191
00:16:47,660 --> 00:16:49,580
Jiya is my friend.

192
00:16:49,660 --> 00:16:51,870
Manu, actually we've just moved in.
Let us settle down first. - Of course.

193
00:16:51,950 --> 00:16:53,370
If you need anything. - Sure.

194
00:16:53,450 --> 00:16:55,120
Please don't hesitate,
I'm just a doorbell away. - Thank you.

195
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:56,370
Shall I make tea for you? - No.

196
00:16:56,450 --> 00:16:57,910
Water..

197
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,700
I'll give it, thank you.
- I want water.

198
00:17:00,450 --> 00:17:02,830
How about coffee..
- No, Thanks, Manu.

199
00:17:05,750 --> 00:17:08,160
He's laughing. - I didn't
arrange the welcome party.

200
00:17:08,250 --> 00:17:09,410
Where's the house?

201
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:10,750
This is going to be
your house for sometime now.

202
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:12,290
100 years later?

203
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:17,370
You are very young.

204
00:17:17,950 --> 00:17:20,450
This is my friend's house,
it's been lying vacant.

205
00:17:20,830 --> 00:17:22,580
We can stay here as long as we want.

206
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:26,290
We? - You, of course.
C'mon, get up now.

207
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:29,540
Come. - Get up. Do this, do that.

208
00:17:29,580 --> 00:17:31,540
I've asked Anu for some time..

209
00:17:31,580 --> 00:17:33,620
..because there's no point
sending you to a clinic.

210
00:17:34,290 --> 00:17:36,950
Being independent again will help
you face this problem. Really.

211
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:40,660
Will you give it a try?

212
00:17:49,870 --> 00:17:51,160
Best keep this one closed.

213
00:18:00,370 --> 00:18:01,540
The bedroom has such a nice view.

214
00:18:02,250 --> 00:18:04,870
Shaan, please close it.
- No, you need vitamin D.

215
00:18:08,290 --> 00:18:09,660
Who does this belong to?

216
00:18:10,580 --> 00:18:14,160
The house belongs to my friend but he
had rented it out to a girl named Jiya.

217
00:18:14,250 --> 00:18:15,950
Some of her clothes and stuff
might be lying around.

218
00:18:16,040 --> 00:18:17,200
Throw away whatever you don't need.

219
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:19,910
What if she comes back for it?
- She won't.

220
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:20,910
What?

221
00:18:21,450 --> 00:18:24,370
She didn't pay the rent,
didn't come to collect her deposit.

222
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:26,160
Maybe she skipped town.

223
00:18:37,830 --> 00:18:39,080
Sorry, chips.

224
00:18:41,910 --> 00:18:43,450
Shall we clean up the place?

225
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:46,330
I'll do it.
Don't you have to go to work?

226
00:18:46,580 --> 00:18:48,580
I thought I'll take my Diwali
leave from today itself.

227
00:18:48,660 --> 00:18:49,700
No need, Shaan.

228
00:18:49,830 --> 00:18:52,120
I'll take some time
out of my busy schedule.

229
00:18:54,080 --> 00:18:56,540
How much is the rent?
- Don't worry about that.

230
00:18:59,450 --> 00:19:02,370
Get well soon, start painting
and you can pay me back, ok?

231
00:19:02,450 --> 00:19:04,500
What did you and
Anusha put in my coffee?

232
00:19:05,450 --> 00:19:06,950
You thought I'll not come to know.

233
00:19:07,540 --> 00:19:09,000
Would you've agreed
if I had asked directly?

234
00:19:11,160 --> 00:19:14,160
If my motor skills don't come back.
I'm not talking to you again.

235
00:19:16,580 --> 00:19:17,830
You should go now.

236
00:19:18,620 --> 00:19:20,080
Don't forget your medicines.

237
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:11,700
"this girl is going to drive me crazy"

238
00:25:09,040 --> 00:25:10,200
Hello?

239
00:26:05,830 --> 00:26:06,950
Don't need

240
00:26:31,660 --> 00:26:32,580
Don't need.

241
00:27:03,410 --> 00:27:05,660
Hi, it's me. Open up. - Wait a second!

242
00:27:07,620 --> 00:27:10,620
I'm opening, but count to ten
before you step in. Ok? - Yeah, ok.

243
00:27:10,910 --> 00:27:12,040
Huh? - Yeah!

244
00:27:12,120 --> 00:27:12,910
Ok.

245
00:27:19,160 --> 00:27:20,410
Shall I come in?

246
00:28:20,870 --> 00:28:21,830
What are you doing?

247
00:28:22,450 --> 00:28:23,250
Nothing.

248
00:28:31,250 --> 00:28:33,620
Hey, dance with me, c'mon.

249
00:28:33,950 --> 00:28:34,870
C'mon. - No, thanks.

250
00:28:34,950 --> 00:28:35,620
C'mon!

251
00:28:36,750 --> 00:28:39,330
What are you doing?
Let me eat. - C'mon, play along.

252
00:28:39,580 --> 00:28:43,120
Ok, fine. I'll watch you dance.
Shaan's got talent - M, c'mon!

253
00:30:12,040 --> 00:30:14,000
It's ok.. it's ok.

254
00:30:14,450 --> 00:30:15,950
